The White House Office of the Press Secretary has released a statement on legislation to ban insider trading by members of Congress. The statement announces that the Senate will be taking up legislation to prevent members of Congress from engaging in insider trading. This legislation is seen as an important part of the President's plan for a sustainable America. The statement highlights the need to limit the influence of money in politics and restore trust in Washington. It emphasizes that members of Congress should not be allowed to trade stocks based on nonpublic information obtained on Capitol Hill, nor should they be able to own stocks in industries they have an impact on. The statement calls for swift passage of the legislation as a crucial first step in preventing members of Congress from profiting from their positions.